## API Contract

### POST `/api/recommend`

**Request:**
```json
{
  "latitude": 28.6139,
  "longitude": 77.2090,
  "mood": "tired",
  "hunger": "full_meal",
  "fitAccessToken": "optional_google_fit_token"
}
```

**Response:**
```json
{
  "contextSummary": "It's a hot afternoon in Delhi and you're feeling tired after minimal activity вҖ” your body needs iron, B-vitamins, and hydrating foods without heavy oils.",
  "rationale": "With the temperature at 38В°C and high humidity, your body is already working hard to cool itself. Being tired compounds the energy drain. Your digestive system needs easily absorbed nutrients вҖ” specifically iron-rich leafy greens and B-vitamin sources like whole grains вҖ” rather than heavy, oil-laden dishes that would further tax your metabolism in this heat.",
  "meals": [
    {
      "rank": 1,
      "name": "Palak dal with cumin-tempered brown rice",
      "cuisine": "Indian",
      "mealType": "Main Course",
      "reason": "Spinach provides the iron your tired body craves while the lentils offer sustained protein without the heaviness of meat in this heat.",
      "nutrients": ["Iron", "B-vitamins", "Plant Protein", "Fiber"]
    },
    {
      "rank": 2,
      "name": "Chilled sesame cucumber noodles with tofu",
      "cuisine": "Chinese",
      "mealType": "Main Course",
      "reason": "Cold noodles are ideal for extreme heat, and sesame provides magnesium to combat fatigue while tofu adds light protein.",
      "nutrients": ["Magnesium", "Protein", "Hydration", "Selenium"]
    }
  ],
  "avoidList": [
    {
      "item": "Deep-fried samosas or pakoras",
      "reason": "Heavy oil increases body heat and slows digestion вҖ” dangerous when you're already fatigued in 38В°C weather."
    },
    {
      "item": "Sugary iced tea or cold coffee",
      "reason": "The sugar crash will worsen your tiredness within 45 minutes, and caffeine can further dehydrate you in this heat."
    }
  ],
  "hydrationTip": "Drink at least 500ml of water with a pinch of salt and lemon juice in the next hour. The heat and your fatigue suggest early signs of mild dehydration.",
  "nextMealHint": "Plan a light evening snack around 6:30 PM вҖ” a small bowl of chilled yogurt with roasted makhana would sustain you without disrupting sleep.",
  "weather": {
    "temperature": 38,
    "humidity": 65,
    "condition": "hot",
    "description": "Partly Cloudy"
  },
  "activity": {
    "steps": 1200,
    "calories": 150,
    "level": "sedentary"
  },
  "timeOfDay": "afternoon_slump"
}
```

